"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The Mirror Editor enables composing entries with media blocks, such as images and videos, along with crypto economic blocks, like crowdfunds and auctions. It uses plain text and [Markdown formatting](https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax) with a few simple formatting conventions.\\n\\n### **Modes**\\nComposition takes place in **`Edit`** mode. To preview your entry as it will appear on your publication enter **`Preview`** mode. You can toggle between them with the related buttons in the toolbar.\\n\\n### **Importing entries**\\nTo import entries from elsewhere, such as Medium or Substack, open the secondary `•••` menu in the navigation, then click **Import entry**. Next, enter the URL to your entry. The url will be parsed into markdown, and set as the content of your entry. Please only import content you have created and own.\\n\\n### **Creating blocks**\\nTo easily create a media or economic block, first click inside your entry to place the curser where you’d like the block to appear. Next, click the **Blocks** area of the Toolbar, or focus with the keyboard shortcut `⌘+/`. The blocks menu will appear, showing you all available blocks. Selecting a block prompts you for secondary information. Once you’re satisfied, confirm the information to insert the block into your entry.\\n\\n## Blocks\\n\\nMedia embeds and economic blocks on Mirror are recognized with a simple formatting convention: an individual link on it’s own line of text. To manually create a block, insert a new line of text, add a link, then add a line break. ***Ensure that the new line only contains a single link***. Here is an example which creates a Youtube video embed.\\n\\n```markdown\\nThe 90-minute presentation essentially demonstrated almost all the fundamental elements of modern personal computing:\\n\\n[The Mother of All Demos](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJDv-zdhzMY)\\n\\nEngelbart's presentation was the first to publicly demonstrate all of these elements in a single system.\\n```\\n\\n[The Mother of All Demos](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FCiBUawCawo)\\n\\nWe’ve decided to parse basic links—as opposed to introducing Mirror specific syntax—to ensure portability. If the markdown is rendered with Mirror you will see a Mirror Block. If anywhere else, you’ll see a simple plain text link. There are a number of integrations, and we’re adding more every week.\\n\\n## NFTs\\n\\nEmbed an NFT by creating a link. Prefix the URL with the `ethereum://` protocol, followed by the `address/id`. Currently supports a images, audio, video, and text embeds. Mirror currently supports EthBlock.art, Foundation, Rarible, SuperRare and Zora.\\n\\n```md\\n[NFT Example](ethereum://0xb932a70a57673d89f4acffbe830e8ed7f75fb9e0/16297)\\n```\\n\\n[NFT Example](ethereum://0xb932a70a57673d89f4acffbe830e8ed7f75fb9e0/16297)\\n\\n## Crowdfund\\n\\nCrowdfund example\\n\\n```md\\n[Burn Alpha](crowdfund://0x95d0A89943E0e3e05d290Fc07462c148EB6a11Ff?network=homestead)\\n```\\n\\n[Burn Alpha](crowdfund://0x95d0A89943E0e3e05d290Fc07462c148EB6a11Ff?network=homestead)\\n\\n## Auction\\n\\n[Create an auction](/dashboard/auctions) and deploy it. After it has been deployed a snippet of code will appear in the `Embed auction` section. Copy and paste this into an entry. It should look like the example below, but with your dedicated auction address and `tokenID`.\\n\\n```md\\n[Token #1522](auction://0xabEFBc9fD2F806065b4f3C237d4b59D9A97Bcac7?network=mainnet&tokenId=1522)\\n```\\n\\n[Token #1522](auction://0xabEFBc9fD2F806065b4f3C237d4b59D9A97Bcac7?network=mainnet&tokenId=1522)\\n\\n## Images\\n\\nEmbedding images is possible by dragging and dropping into the editor, selecting **Image** in the blocks menu, or manually creating a markdown image tag. Reserving the space of the image prior to loading is possible by defining the `width` and `height` query parameters, which are automatically set when uploading an image to Mirror.\\n\\n```md\\n![Image caption](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/589ec9e9-59a2-4505-ba83-35210d01c223.jpeg?height=1180&width=1588)\\n```\\n\\n![Image caption](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/589ec9e9-59a2-4505-ba83-35210d01c223.jpeg?height=1180&width=1588)\\n\\n## Link previews\\n\\nMirror displays a progressively enhanced preview of all links based on the universal standard of [OpenGraph tags](https://ogp.me).\\n\\n```md\\n[Mirror](https://mirror.xyz)\\n```\\n\\n[Mirror](https://mirror.xyz)\\n\\n## Twitter\\n\\nEmbed an individual Tweet or an entire Tweet thread by inserting a link to any Twitter URL.\\n\\n```md\\n[Mirror’s first tweet](https://twitter.com/viamirror/status/1325856116748726273)\\n```\\n\\n[Mirror’s first tweet](https://twitter.com/viamirror/status/1325856116748726273)\\n\\n## Youtube\\n\\n```md\\n[Powers of Ten](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0fKBhvDjuy0)\\n```\\n\\n[Powers of Ten](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0fKBhvDjuy0)\\n\\n## Video embeds\\n\\nEmbed an `.mp4` video by inserting a link to an externally hosted video file. It is also possible to set `autoplay`, `muted`, `loop` and `controls` by setting the related query parameters. Ensure you manually define the `width` and `height` parameters to reserve the vertical space for your video.\\n\\n```md\\n[Powers of Ten](https://jkm-library.s3.amazonaws.com/blocks/powers-of-10.mp4?height=480&width=640&autoplay=true&loop=true&muted=true)\\n```\\n\\n[Powers of Ten](https://jkm-library.s3.amazonaws.com/blocks/powers-of-10.mp4?height=480&width=640&autoplay=true&loop=true&muted=true)\\n\\n## iFrames\\n\\nIt’s possible to embed any page by creating an iFrame block. This is useful when for embedding interactive WebGL content, for example. Simply set `display=iframe` as a query parameter.\\n\\n```md\\n[ThreeJS Demo](https://threejs.org/examples/webgl_water_flowmap.html?display=iframe)\\n```\\n\\n[ThreeJS Demo](https://threejs.org/examples/webgl_water_flowmap.html?display=iframe)\\n\\n## Layout sizes\\n\\nIf you’re looking to create a more editorial layout for your entry, consider setting custom layout sizes for certain media blocks. Supported block types include Image, Video, Youtube and iFrame.\\n\\nThe block size is set with a query parameter, and it is possible to choose from both `medium` and `large`. For example, below is a `large` image which extends to the edges of the page.\\n\\n```md\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/da461938-5ccf-4397-aa6d-d082cbba2128.jpeg?height=1533&width=2300&size=large)\\n```\\n\\n![](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/layouts.svg?height=402&width=897)\\n\\n\\n## Future enhancements\\n\\nMirror is a new project, and our editor is intentionally focused as we move fast to create new economic tools to fund great writing. In time we plan to introduce a new editor which enables enables editing in place, removing the need to toggle between edit and preview modes. Until then, we appreciate your patience, and [welcome any feedback](https://discord.gg/6d7tsjPBjS).\",\"timestamp\":1618449545,\"title\":\"Editor Guide\",\"publication\":\"jktest\"},\"digest\":\"VGBhltB-4TFQCp6suKzgkKOLIOZOlMQCsT_kT2VAyT4\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x841fF85B6873d7bfB712C8f7A347C774355b6EC3\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"h6AcsD2ipLIcdXf3TKQyglsvS_D0gQ5rQdZWyyDxqxg\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"AUl9j4iWw73csrORK2yLe4DO0bB41e59cbTCm37IdTY\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"MNuyOyRdRUiOWUmryf3SBqh0DFMkRUKYFhG-oqwCdqbza_KoYyM6rzYhWBkL_dVbjRVaaP62nvnT-bvcG_WCtg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x2caf0d2eea72f8a00635dbf6e5aeca046c10c3a5e16744a22f573e1c416e8cca7844c18bb6ac0dd7abe3fa9df8b91d2a8f083214730f771d64c7f0cd160afd4d1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize the publication of articles on jktest2.mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"h6AcsD2ipLIcdXf3TKQyglsvS_D0gQ5rQdZWyyDxqxg\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"AUl9j4iWw73csrORK2yLe4DO0bB41e59cbTCm37IdTY\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"fMzen4XH0ez6PIu2H7c_ynrLyTajh41rPVIkSVaqDsE\"}"